description: Naomi is a snooty, cow villager in the Animal Crossing series. She first appeared in Animal Crossing: New Leaf. Her name is from the Bible and means "pleasant"; it also can mean "honest and beautiful" in Japanese, referencing how snooty villagers like looking beautiful. Her catchphrase, "moolah," is a play on the slang word "moola," meaning "money." It is also similar to the catchphrase of Petunia, another snooty cow villager.
